revision.text:
{{Infobox person | name = Adlan Khasanov | image = Adlan Khasanov.jpg | caption = Adlan Khasanov | birthname = | birth_date = {{birth date|1970|05|25}} | birth_place = [[Chechnya]] | age = | death_date = {{death date and age|2004|05|09|1970|05|25}} | death_place = Grozny | occupation = [[Photojournalism]] | alias = | status = | title = | family = | spouse = | children = | relatives = | religion = | salary = | networth = | URL = | agent = }} '''Adlan Khasanov''' (May 25, 1970 – May 9, 2004) was a [[Chechnya|Chechen]], [[Russia]]n [[journalist]] and [[photographer]], killed in action in [[Grozny]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20050802103135/http://www.nppa.org/news_and_events/news/2004/05/reuters_photojournalist_killed.html Reuters Photojournalist Adlan Khasanov Killed With President in Chechen Bomb Blast]</ref>
Khasanov studied journalism at the [[Chechen State University]], and later worked in newspapers as a reporter and photographer. He also worked for [[Reuters]] and [[RFE/RL|Radio Liberty]].
He was killed during a 9 May [[Victory Day]] [[parade]] at the "Dynamo" stadium in Grozny, in a bomb blast carried out by Chechen separatists in an attempt to eliminate Kremlin-backed Chechen President [[Akhmad Kadyrov]]. The stadium had undergone remodeling and reconstruction, and, according to reports, a bomb placed inside a concrete part of the structure escaped [[Explosive detection|security detection]] sweeps.
==See also== * [[List of journalists killed in Russia]]
