{{multiple issues| {{BLP sources|date=January 2015}} {{more footnotes|date=January 2015}} }} {{Use dmy dates|date=November 2013}} {{Infobox boxer | name = Ben Tackie | nationality = Ghanaian | realname = Benjamin Tackie | nickname = Wonder | weight = [[Welterweight]] | height= 5 ft 9 in | reach = {{convert|71|in|cm|1|abbr=on}} | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1973|7|23}} | birth_place = [[Accra]], Ghana | style = [[Orthodox Stance|Orthodox]] | total = 44 | wins = 31 | KO = 17 | losses = 13 | draws = | no contests = }}
'''Benjamin "Ben" Tackie''' (born 23 July 1973) is a Ghanaian [[professional boxer]] and world title challenger. He is known for his excellent [[chin (combat sports)|chin]] and ability to throw a high volume of punches. All but one of his losses have come via decision.
==Professional career== Known as "Wonder", Tackie turned pro in 1994 and won his first 18 fights before losing a decision to [[Gregorio Vargas]] in 1999. In 2002 he took on Kostya Tszyu for the unified WBC, WBA, and IBF light welterweight titles but lost a decision. He lost his next two fights to [[Sharmba Mitchell]] and [[Ricky Hatton]]. He lost his most recent bout to [[Matthew Hatton]] on 22 September 2008 on the undercard to [[Ricky Hatton]]'s Light Welterweight title defence in Las Vegas.
Tackie's 10th-round knockout of [[Roberto Garcia Cortez|Roberto Garcia]] was named [[Ring Magazine]] [[Knockout of the Year]] for 2000.
So far in his 41 pro fights Tackie has been knocked down only once.
==Stalking charge==
In February 2015, his Stalking conviction was reversed in Bronx county court in New York. The threat communicated "Don't let me use my boxing skills on you" apparently did not rise to the legal requirement to uphold his conviction. http://law.justia.com/cases/new-york/other-courts/2015/2015-ny-slip-op-50117-u.html <ref>http://law.justia.com/cases/new-york/other-courts/2015/2015-ny-slip-op-50117-u.html</ref>
==Statistics== As of April 2009 his record stands at 29-11-1 with 17 knockouts.
